{"id":771,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":771,"title":"Leah","subtitle":"","short_title":"Leah","uri":"/scriptures/bd/leah","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/leah.t1","order":".000.2041"},[".title","Leah"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/leah.p1","order":".000.2042"},["i","Weary."],"Eldest daughter of Laban. She became Jacob’s wife through a trick of Laban’s, who passed her off as his daughter Rachel; being veiled, the mistake was not discovered till after the marriage had taken place (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/29"},"Gen. 29"],"). She became the mother of six sons and one daughter (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/29.30-32"},"Gen. 29:30–32"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/30.17-21"},"30:17–21"],"; see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/31.4,14,33"},"31:4, 14, 33"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/33.1-2,7"},"33:1–2, 7"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/35.23,26"},"35:23, 26"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/49.31"},"49:31"],")."]]],"refs":null}
